<br>
The difference, is about a guild's-worth (no not their ability) since you want to be extremely picky about it. At the time Forager/Hunter only required at best 1 person or even group. Same for VP keys minus the need for an item from a rotation mob. Same for POJ trials. These could be done (minus trak) with a pick-up group.<br>
The comparison you are trying to draw Barrd (and several others here), or at least it seems that way.. is that &quot;the needs of the few or the one outweigh the needs of the many&quot;.<br>
<br>
You might suggest that the guild's that are trying to keep the tier boss mobs within the spirit of the rotational guidelines are attempting the same by trying to 'keep' people from accessing content (which is a farce at best.. open your eyes.) when in fact they are not.<br>
<br>
The contentation is that since the &quot;gatekeepers&quot; for the next tier planes do in fact give a loot-like 'item' and since having access to the new tier's gives someone access to items they would not normally have access to if they killed a tier boss mob (eg: aerin dar) with an alliance of guilds, the issue arises that the guilds that did not ally to kill the tier boss mobs in order to keep the principles of rotational mobs (regardless if they exist on the RTA rotations page or not) in check contest that those that do form an alliance for these 'flag/item' giving mobs and only for these mobs are being unfair to a part of the community.<br>
<br>
What you might think is 'fair' for all, may in fact only be 'fair' for you. It's all about sharing fairly. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/btherathetravelagency.showUserPublicProfile?gid=darkoak>DarkOak</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_fire.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Noble Blade</span><br>  Posts: 504<br> <font color=#00FFFF>(2/27/03 5:33 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub6.ezboard.com/ftherathetravelagencyfrm50.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=534.topic&index=175>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   ..</span><hr size=1> <!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr><br>
