<br>
At one time, VP *was* under a rotation system.<br>
<br>
<br>
&quot;Also, as stated before, even when Seb was at it's busiest, there was never a mention of folks having to have &quot;permission&quot; or going against the spirit of the RTA by doing the Hunter/Forager cycle with a pick-up group. How is this any different than those two?&quot;<br>
<br>
The same reason as regular xp mobs aren't under rotation.  Spawn time is instantaneous and the mobs can be solo'd by many classes.  You don't have to declare an alliance to kill one of these mobs.  Alliances are formed to kill Severilous, which is arguably much easier than any of the bosses in PoP.<br>
<br>
Basically it is this: if you combine forces to kill a boss, then you have formed an alliance.  When you form an alliance, all of your rotation slots are merged.  Dissolve your alliance and your rotation slots are deleted, you have to get back on the rotations that you want into.  Working around the system will earn you and your guild a bad reputation with all the other guilds who support the system and feel that it has value.  You are simply exploiting the spirit of the agreements that everyone has made (and agreed to by participation in the rotational system).<br>
<br>
Bucking the system is simply a way of stating that you aren't happy with the system.  Usually this comes from not understanding why the system (and perhaps many of its archaic pieces) have come about.  &quot;Why are the planes on the reservation system?&quot;  &quot;Why can't we ignore alliance rules now?&quot;  Sure... times have changed.  Rules should be modified to take them into account but not necessarily remove the spirit in which they were made.<br>
<br>
Why are there alliance rules: Simply because it was an agreement put into place to try to maintain fairness for everyone who agreed to play by those rules. Example, two guilds are capable of killing MobX on their own.  Three guilds form an alliance to kill MobX (none of them are able to tackle the beast on their own).  Should the rotation then be GuildA, GuildB, AllianceA, AllianceA, AllianceA?  I hope that you can see how GuildA and GuildB would consider this unfair.<br>
<br>
Sure... the way to work around the system is to form an &quot;alliance&quot; for one night to get what you want done.  Most folks see this for what it is - simply working around the system.  I'm also sure you would see how folks who have worked within the rules that were agreed upon would not like to see abusing the system in this way and why they would not like to see it.<br>
<br>
Our rotation is what has kept many of us sane over the years of playing this game.  Do we love the system?  Most actually do not love it.  However, we know that it is better than the alternative which is basically playing the game like almost all other servers play.  Incidentally, a good friend of mine who plays on Povar has been telling me how a number of the smaller guilds have come together (very) recently to basically create a rotational system on some mobs so that folks have a chance to experience the content in the game.<br>
<br>
Yes, the rotational system does protect the interests of the guilds who are capable of certain content.  However, our rotational system also allows any other group to enter into the rotation and have their interests protected as well.  Is it a barrier to advancement? In some cases, it arguably is (the 40 people PoFear/PoHate rules) but there were reasons for that at the time (the constant requests for CR help) which may be outdated now.  But... for all other mobs, it is not a barrier as the only thing you have to do is have your guild/alliance kill the mob and you are in.  The content is the barrier you fight against.  Are you capable of killing the mob to be &quot;registered&quot; to have your group's interests protected from the larger guilds (by preserving a rotation slot for you)?  In relation to Behemoth, there is no reason to kill the Behemoth to get into PoTactics as entry can be gained through a quest.  The only reason to kill Behemoth is to gain a flag for advancement further into PoP - something that can be done any period of time after gaining access to PoTactics when your guild/alliance is strong enough to tackle Behemoth on your own (for further advancement into PoP).<br>
<br>
Interestingly enough... the focus of all this has been on PoP encounters when there is another encounter exactly like these in SoL (The Emperor of Ssra) which we hear almost nothing about.  Why are these different? <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/btherathetravelagency.showUserPublicProfile?gid=zaken51>Zaken51</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 12<br> <font color=#00FFFF>(2/27/03 6:34 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub6.ezboard.com/ftherathetravelagencyfrm50.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=534.topic&index=177>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: why?</span><hr size=1> Well Gromm,<br>
<br>
The differences are that we are talking about individual advancement.  We are talking about flagging individuals so they may broaden the zones they may have experience opportunities in.  We are not talking about getting entrance into VT so that a guild can progress in a raiding situation.<br>
<br>
Secondly, we are talking about a clearly defined rotation mob.  I have no arguements against the rotation system as I recognize the civility of it.  At the current time there is no defined rotation rules set in place for these mobs.  And (IMO) doing so would be silly.  As I have stated before, the time/effort into killing these mobs over and over again is probably not worth it to most guilds.  We are talking about a one time/one kill flag.<br>
<br>
Let me just ask another question.  What if 72 individuals were to do a &quot;pickup&quot; raid to one of these mobs.  Would those 72 people now be bound to each other to experience all other content from hence forth.  Would they be forced to leave their current guild and form a new guild in order to explore older and newer content? <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#222222><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/btherathetravelagency.showUserPublicProfile?gid=emilsinclair>Emil Sinclair</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Administrator</span><br>  Posts: 369<br> <font color=#00FFFF>(2/27/03 6:58 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub6.ezboard.com/ftherathetravelagencyfrm50.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=534.topic&index=178>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: why?</span><hr size=1> what if 72 people did a pick-up aow?<br>
