It's done as a courtesy and it is not like 30 people from another guild show up.  It is usually less than four.  Again, read what it said - only if your guild has already successfully defeated the mob will this courtesy be extended to you.  Plus, there *is* a difference (a very big difference) in the two situations.  In one case you have a mob of folks doing something that may be currently out of their reach.  In the other, you have two (or more) entities who have already proven that they are capable, independently, of the content.  Also, what you don't know about it is that in those cases, when able/feasible, the other guild folks sit at the zone until the encounter is over then get CotH to get flagged.  They don't actually participate in the actual encounter itself.<br>
<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>I just have a problem with the theme I am seeing. As I stated previously I personally am not interested in joining forces to get my flag for these zones. I do not have a problem going the alternate route, or waiting until my guild can accomplish this task. What I do have a problem with is the theme of &quot;we don't want you here because we like our little place to ourselves&quot; attitude and using a political agenda to keep it that way.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
I don't know what really to say about this.  When you have something &quot;unspoiled&quot; you like to keep it that way.  The rotation system is about trying to be fair, not about cuddling folks and altruistically ushering everyone through the content.  It's about making sure folks have access in a way that is considered fair by all involved - from the uber side and from the up-and-coming side.  Each side makes some compromises for the &quot;better good&quot;. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/btherathetravelagency.showUserPublicProfile?gid=grommofbots>Gromm of BotS</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Blood of the Spider</span><br>  Posts: 247<br> <font color=#00FFFF>(2/27/03 10:26 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub6.ezboard.com/ftherathetravelagencyfrm50.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=534.topic&index=194>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: .</span><hr size=1> <!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>BoTS, FK, TL, NB, ED do not need to go onto the rotation as they have their flags and guildmates won't need them that don't have them unless they start to get a large number of members who need the flags.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
